author_ssm: Camille M. Purcell (1991) and Porsche Martin (2002).
abstract_ssm: Herman and Conway Associates was a labor relations consulting firm founded in the 1940's as a successor to Robert Maisel Associates. In its work on behalf of employees and employer associations, the firm dealt with the major labor and management relations issues that pervaded the post-World War II era. The collection includes some of the the firm's correspondence, memorandums and clippings.
